From 3054912264d54d44a07521cfba7e906930ee1899 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ci <ci@ask>
Date: Mon, 18 May 2026 11:11:41 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fman/pcd: surface hmct_bytes_used on chain handle
 (PR14-hmct-bytes / P1)

Add fman_pcd_manip_chain_hmct_bytes_used() as a NULL-safe accessor over
the chain->hmct_used field that patch 0036 already populates.

This is an additive, optional-output accessor: per
kernel/flavors/ask/patches/README.md 'FMAN_PCD_API_VERSION bump rule'
no API version bump is required (no struct-layout change, no new
required argument, in-tree writers continue to populate the field
unconditionally).

Use cases:
  - cc_encode_ad() can pre-flight whether a chain fits in one AD slot
    vs needs the multi-AD walker (single-AD threshold ~32 B per RM
    8.7.4.3).
  - The MURAM budget counter in ask_hw can charge actual byte cost,
    not the worst-case FMAN_PCD_HMCT_CHAIN_SIZE upper bound.
  - cat /sys/kernel/debug/fman_pcd/<n>/manip becomes a useful
    capacity-planning tool.

Signed-off-by: ASK2 CI <ci@ask>
---
 .../ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_manip.c  | 38 +++++++++++++++++++
 include/linux/fsl/fman_pcd.h                  | 12 ++++++
 2 files changed, 50 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_manip.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_manip.c
index 62c9eea..543bb19 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_manip.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_manip.c
@@ -1048,6 +1048,44 @@ unsigned long fman_pcd_manip_hmtd_off(const struct fman_pcd_manip *manip)
 	return manip->hmtd_off;
 }
 
+/**
+ * fman_pcd_manip_chain_hmct_bytes_used() - read the chain's active-HMCT byte count.
+ * @chain: chain handle from fman_pcd_manip_chain_create().  NULL-safe.
+ *
+ * Returns the number of HMCT bytes actually consumed by the
+ * concatenated command sequence (the sum of every contained manip's
+ * hmct_used at chain-create time).  Always <= FMAN_PCD_HMCT_CHAIN_SIZE
+ * (256 B silicon hard limit per RM 8.11.4 + worst-case 4 manips at
+ * 56 B each = 224 B).
+ *
+ * Use cases (P1 - debuggability + capacity planning):
+ *   - cc_encode_ad() can pre-flight whether a chain fits in one AD
+ *     slot vs needs the multi-AD walker (single-AD threshold ~32 B
+ *     per RM 8.7.4.3).
+ *   - The MURAM budget counter in ask_hw can charge actual byte
+ *     cost, not the worst-case FMAN_PCD_HMCT_CHAIN_SIZE upper bound.
+ *   - `cat /sys/kernel/debug/fman_pcd/<n>/manip` becomes a useful
+ *     capacity-planning tool.
+ *
+ * Returns 0 if @chain is NULL (sentinel, NOT a legal value - a real
+ * chain always has at least one contained manip with hmct_used >=
+ * 4 bytes per the validator in fman_pcd_manip_chain_create()).
+ *
+ * This is an additive accessor: the field it reads is already
+ * populated by the chain-create path landed in patch 0036 / PR14x.
+ * Per kernel/flavors/ask/patches/README.md "FMAN_PCD_API_VERSION
+ * bump rule" this does NOT require bumping FMAN_PCD_API_VERSION
+ * (no struct-layout change, no new required argument, in-tree
+ * writers continue to populate the field unconditionally).
+ */
+size_t fman_pcd_manip_chain_hmct_bytes_used(const struct fman_pcd_manip *chain)
+{
+	if (!chain)
+		return 0;
+	return chain->hmct_used;
+}
+EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(fman_pcd_manip_chain_hmct_bytes_used);
+
 
 /* ------------------------------------------------------------------ */
 /* PR14x: chained-manip primitive                                     */
diff --git a/include/linux/fsl/fman_pcd.h b/include/linux/fsl/fman_pcd.h
index eff86c3..04c82ea 100644
--- a/include/linux/fsl/fman_pcd.h
+++ b/include/linux/fsl/fman_pcd.h
@@ -730,6 +730,18 @@ fman_pcd_manip_chain_create(struct fman_pcd *pcd,
  */
 void fman_pcd_manip_chain_destroy(struct fman_pcd_manip *chain);
 
+/**
+ * fman_pcd_manip_chain_hmct_bytes_used() - read the chain's active HMCT byte count.
+ * @chain: chain handle from fman_pcd_manip_chain_create().  NULL-safe.
+ *
+ * See implementation kerneldoc in fman_pcd_manip.c for the full
+ * contract.  TL;DR: returns the sum of every contained manip's
+ * hmct_used at chain-create time, in bytes, always <= 256.  Used
+ * by ask.ko for MURAM budget accounting and single-AD vs multi-AD
+ * walk pre-flight decisions.  Returns 0 on NULL @chain.
+ */
+size_t fman_pcd_manip_chain_hmct_bytes_used(const struct fman_pcd_manip *chain);
+
 /* ----------------------------------------------------------------------
  * Policer profiles (fman_pcd_plcr.c, PR14e)
